%5B%7B%22title%22%3A%22A%20Colorado%20police%20department%20cut%20staff's%20hours%20by%2020%25%20without%20reducing%20their%20pay.%20A%20sergeant%20says%20he%20has%20more%20time%20to%20watch%20his%20kids%20play%20sport%20and%20goes%20to%20work%20in%20a%20better%20mood.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225130%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Policeman%20in%20uniform%20in%20US%20giving%20driver%20speeding%20ticket%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F659beb411c5c7b8c9a0eb710%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223420%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EAriel%20Skelley%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20City%20of%20Golden%20Police%20Department%20moved%20all%20staff%20to%20a%2032-hour%20schedule%2C%20including%20the%20chief.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EStaff%20are%20still%20paid%20the%20same.%20Employee%20retention%20has%20improved%2C%20Sergeant%20Ben%20Salentine%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ESalentine%20says%20he%20has%20time%20to%20watch%20his%20kid's%20sporting%20matches%20and%20go%20to%20the%20gym.%20He%20also%20goes%20to%20work%C2%A0%26quot%3Bin%20a%20better%20mood.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EA%20police%20department%20in%20a%20small%20city%20near%20Denver%20cut%20staff's%20hours%20by%2020%25%20without%20reducing%20their%20pay%20as%20part%20of%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcolorado-police-department-4-day-workweek-staff-golden-jobs-productivity-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efour-day%20workweek%20trial%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20City%20of%20Golden%20started%20the%20pilot%20program%20in%20July%2C%20which%20generally%20cut%20employees'%20workweeks%20from%2040%20to%2032%20hours.%20All%20roughly%2070%20employees%20at%20the%20city's%20police%20department%20are%20taking%20part%20in%20the%20program%2C%20including%20the%20police%20chief.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20badged%20staff%20who%20typically%20worked%20four%2010-%20or%2012-hour%20shifts%20and%20administrative%20staff%20who%20worked%20five%20eight-hour%20shifts%20now%20work%20four%20eight-hour%20shifts%20each%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20trial%20was%20originally%20set%20to%20end%20in%20December.%20But%20it's%20still%20ongoing%2C%20and%20could%20be%20introduced%20to%20other%20city%20departments%2C%20Sergeant%20Ben%20Salentine%2C%20who%20heads%20up%20the%20department's%20public%20information%20work%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20The%20program%20was%20initially%20introduced%20with%20the%20hopes%20of%20expanding%20it%20citywide.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20reason%20why%20they%20did%20the%20police%20department%20right%20away%20is%20because%20we%20have%20the%20most%20diverse%20work%20schedules%3A%2024%20hours%20a%20day%2C%20seven%20days%20a%20week%2C%26quot%3B%20Salentine%20said%20during%20a%20phone%20interview.%20%26quot%3BSo%20if%20we%20could%20make%20it%20work%2C%20the%20hope%20was%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20city%20could%20as%20well.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESalentine%20said%20that%20when%20the%20police%20department%20first%20proposed%20cutting%20employees'%20hours%2C%20some%20were%20concerned%20about%20how%20it%20could%20affect%20their%20careers.%20But%20almost%20all%20are%20now%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F4-day-workweek-evidence-prevent-burnout-productivity-ai-well-being-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esupportive%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20new%20schedules%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey're%20getting%20paid%20the%20same%20amount%20of%20money%20for%20working%20less%20hours%20during%20a%20workweek%20and%20they%20can%20choose%20to%20use%20those%20hours%20how%20they%20see%20fit%2C%26quot%3B%20Salentine%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20a%20pretty%20positive%20benefit.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStaff%20working%20in%20administrative%20roles%20were%20allowed%20input%20on%20which%20day%20they%20wanted%20off%20each%20week%2C%20though%20a%20supervisor%20made%20the%20final%20call%20on%20the%20schedule%2C%20Salentine%20said.%20Some%20workers%20wanted%20Mondays%20or%20Fridays%20off%20so%20they%20could%20have%20a%20longer%20weekend%2C%20while%20others%20wanted%20Wednesdays%20off%20to%20break%20up%20their%20week%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESalentine%20has%20personally%20felt%20the%20benefits%20of%20his%20shorter%20workweek.%20%26quot%3BI've%20had%20zero%20issue%20with%20seeing%20my%20child's%20sporting%20events%2C%20going%20to%20family%20events%2C%26quot%3B%20Salentine%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BI've%20had%20a%20higher%20level%20of%20ability%20to%20be%20relaxed%20at%20home.%20I%20come%20in%20a%20little%20bit%20more%20refreshed.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20that%20he%20often%20used%20the%20extra%20two%20hours%20he%20had%20off%20a%20day%20to%20visit%20the%20gym.%20%26quot%3BI%20get%20home%20and%20then%20I'm%20better%20for%20my%20spouse%2C%20I'm%20better%20for%20my%20child%2C%20and%20then%20hopefully%20I%20show%20up%20to%20work%20the%20next%20day%20in%20a%20better%20mood%20as%20well%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%20it's%20been%20a%20pretty%20dramatic%20positive%20change%20for%20me.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESalentine%20said%20that%20law%20enforcement%20was%20generally%20hard%20to%20recruit%20for.%20But%20since%20introducing%20the%20four-day%20workweek%20trial%2C%20Golden's%20police%20department%20had%20better%20employee%20retention%20and%20was%20almost%20fully%20staffed%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGolden%20City%20Manager%20Scott%20Vargo%20previously%20said%20that%20the%20police%20department%20would%20maintain%20productivity%20levels%20by%20using%20technology%20and%20automation%2C%20making%20sure%20staff%20didn't%20carry%20out%20personal%20errands%20during%20working%20time%2C%20and%20removing%20distractions%20like%20email%20alerts.%20An%20important%20part%20of%20the%20revised%20operations%20was%20having%20fewer%2C%20shorter%20meetings%20with%20only%20the%20necessary%20staff%20present.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%20nof