C%20the%20pilot%2C%20Captain%20Timothy%20Lancaster%2C%20was%20unexpectedly%20sucked%20out%20of%20the%20aircraft%2C%20clinging%20perilously%20to%20the%20window%20frame%20for%20a%20tension-filled%2020%20minutes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20occurrence%20of%20sudden%20and%20explosive%20decompressions%20in%20an%20airplane%20poses%20a%20serious%20threat%20to%20the%20lives%20of%20those%20on%20board.%20However%2C%20defying%20all%20odds%2C%20the%20captain%20managed%20to%20survive%20the%20ordeal%2C%20eventually%20recounting%20the%20incredible%20story%20of%20his%20survival.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F1990%2F06%2F11%2Fworld%2F4-miles-over-britain-pilot-is-sucked-out-crew-holds-on-tight.html%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ENew%20York%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20flight%20was%20reasonably%20well%20loaded%20on%20the%20day%20of%20the%20incident%2C%20with%2081%20passengers%20and%20six%20crew.%20Flight%20BA5390%20was%20operated%20by%20the%20stretched%20BAC%201-11-500.%20This%20had%20a%20maximum%20capacity%20of%20119%20passengers%20seated%20five%20abreast.%20It%20departed%20Birmingham%20at%2008%3A20%20local%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E13%20minutes%20into%20its%20journey%20from%20Birmingham%2C%20the%20aircraft%20was%20soaring%20at%20an%20altitude%20of%2017%2C300%20feet%20above%20the%20quaint%20railway%20town%20of%20Didcot%2C%20Oxfordshire%2C%20precisely%20at%2008%3A33.%20It%20was%20at%20this%20juncture%20that%20the%20narrative%20of%20BA%205390%20took%20a%20drastic%20and%20ominous%20twist.%20The%20windscreen%20on%20Captain%20Lancaster's%20side%20abruptly%20detached%20from%20the%20aircraft%2C%20accompanied%20by%20a%20loud%20and%20explosive%20sound.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3EIn%201990%2C%20the%20windshield%20of%20British%20Airways%20Flight%205390%20came%20off%20at%20an%20altitude%20of%2017%2C000%20feet.%20This%20triggered%20a%20sudden%20decompression%20in%20the%20cockpit%2C%20resulting%20in%20the%20captain%20being%20partially%20ejected%20out%20of%20the%20aircraft.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnAs%20luck%20would%20have%20it%2C%20Nigel%20Ogden%2C%20a%20flight%20attendant%2C%E2%80%A6%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FnULmfc2Pbl%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2FnULmfc2Pbl%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%E2%80%94%20Fascinating%20(%40fasc1nate)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Ffasc1nate%2Fstatus%2F1744099628935749933%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EJanuary%207%2C%202024%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20harrowing%20sequence%20of%20events%2C%20the%20abrupt%20and%20explosive%20decompression%20resulting%20from%20the%20detached%20window%20propelled%20Captain%20Lancaster%20headfirst%20out%20of%20the%20ascending%20aircraft.%20Fortunately%2C%20he%20managed%20to%20snag%20his%20legs%20on%20the%20flight%20controls%2C%20preventing%20a%20complete%20ejection.%20Nevertheless%2C%20this%20action%20disengaged%20the%20autopilot%2C%20compelling%20the%20plane%20into%20a%20descent.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20co-pilot%2C%20Alistair%20Atcheson%2C%20swiftly%20donned%20an%20oxygen%20mask%20and%20took%20control%20of%20the%20aircraft.%20Meanwhile%2C%20on%20the%20flight%20deck%2C%20steward%20Nigel%20Ogden%20secured%20Captain%20Lancaster's%20legs%2C%20clinging%20to%20a%20chair%20for%20support.%20Simon%20Rogers%2C%20another%20steward%2C%20hurried%20onto%20the%20flight%20deck%2C%20strapped%20himself%20into%20the%20pilot's%20seat%2C%20and%20relieved%20Mr%20Ogden%2C%20who%20sustained%20a%20hand%20injury%20while%20attempting%20to%20rescue%20the%20captain.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20assistance%20from%20fellow%20crew%20members%2C%20Mr%20Rogers%20maintained%20his%20grip%20on%20the%20captain%20until%20the%20aircraft%20safely%20landed.%20Other%20crew%20members%20reassured%20passengers%2C%20instructing%20them%20to%20fasten%20their%20seatbelts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%2