3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erose%20by%20at%20least%204%25%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%2012%20months%20to%20November%2C%20meaning%20the%20central%20bank%20hasn't%20achieved%20its%20goal%20yet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20idea%20that%20they%20would%20sit%20up%20there%20at%204.1%25%20...%20and%20actually%20do%20any%20kind%20of%20a%20cut%20in%20March%20I%20think%20is%20a%20dream%2C%20it's%20just%20a%20fairy%20tale%20at%20this%20point%2C%26quot%3B%20O'Leary%20said.%20He%20attributed%20the%20dip%20in%20stocks%20this%20year%20to%20investors%20realizing%20%26quot%3Bthe%20Fed%20won't%20be%20cutting%20as%20fast%20as%20anybody%20thinks.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPandemic%20stimulus%20measures%20and%20supply-chain%20snarls%20fueled%20a%20spike%20in%20inflation%20to%209.1%25%20in%20the%20summer%20of%202022%2C%20a%2040-year%20high.%20The%20Fed%20has%20reacted%20by%20hiking%20rates%20from%20virtually%20zero%20to%20over%205%25%2C%20as%20steeper%20rates%20encourage%20saving%20over%20spending%20and%20raise%20borrowing%20costs%2C%20which%20typically%20relieves%20upward%20pressure%20on%20prices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20higher%20rates%20tend%20to%20weigh%20on%20stocks%20and%20other%20risky%20assets%2C%20as%20larger%2C%20guaranteed%20yields%20from%20safe%20assets%20like%20Treasury%20bonds%20entice%20investors%20to%20hold%20those%20instead.%20They%20also%20raise%20the%20risk%20of%20a%20recession%20by%20deterring%20spending%2C%20hiring%2C%20and%20investing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYet%20the%20US%20economy%20grew%20nearly%205%25%20in%20the%20third%20quarter%20of%202023%2C%20unemployment%20has%20remained%20at%20historic%20lows%20of%20below%204%25%20for%20months%2C%20and%20the%20benchmark%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20and%20Nasdaq%20Composite%20indices%20gained%2024%25%20and%2044%25%20respectively%20last%20year.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20inflation%20has%20moved%20closer%20to%20the%20Fed's%20target%20rate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGiven%20the%20relatively%20strong%20backdrop%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20probability%20of%20a%20soft%20landing%20remains%20at%20least%2050-50%2C%26quot%3B%20O'Leary%20said.%20However%2C%20he%20warned%20that%20many%20US%20small%20business%20are%20struggling%20in%20the%20face%20of%20steeper%20borrowing%20costs%20and%20reduced%20access%20to%20credit%2C%20as%20regional%20banks%20have%20pulled%20back%20after%20a%20trio%20of%20lenders%20failed%20last%20spring.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20cracks%20are%20showing%20there%20first%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20experts%20have%20also%20raised%20the%20alarm%2C%20warning%20investors%20to%20brace%20for%20trouble.%20Veteran%20economists%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frecession-forecast-rosenberg-economy-fed-dotcom-housing-bubbles-yield-curve-2024-1%5C%22%3EDavid%20Rosenberg%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fstock-market-outlook-spx-recession-forecast-shilling-fed-rate-cuts-2024-1%5C%22%3EGary%20Shilling%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20pointed%20to%20the%20inverted%20yield%20curve%2C%20shrinking%20money%20supply%2C%20and%20declines%20in%20leading%20economic%20indicators%20as%20signs%20that%20stocks%20are%20poised%20to%20fall%20and%20a%20recession%20will%20probably%20strike.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fshark-tank-kevin-oleary-fed-rate-cuts-economy-inflation-recession-2024-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704714066000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F624f2779fabc73001868d75f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fshark-tank-kevin-oleary-fed-rate-cuts-economy-inflation-recession-2024-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Stocks%20have%20dipped%20this%20year%20as%20investors%20have%20realized%20inflation%20remains%20well%20above%20the%20Fed's%20target%2C%20so%20the%20central%20bank%20won't%20cut%20rates%20imminently.%22%2C%2