ked%20staff%20out%20while%20they%20worked%20and%20didn't%20pay%20overtime%2C%20the%20DOL%20claims.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20DOL%20said%20it%20had%20recovered%20%2426%2C927%20in%20back%20wages%20and%20liquidated%20damages%20for%2036%20employees.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Checkers%20franchisee%20in%20Montgomery%2C%20Alabama%20let%20managers%20at%20two%20restaurants%20clock%20staff%20out%20while%20they%20were%20still%20working%20and%20altered%20their%20timecards%2C%20meaning%20that%20they%20were%20paid%20less%20than%20they%20should%20have%20been%2C%20the%20Department%20of%20Labor%20claimds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20DOL%20said%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dol.gov%2Fnewsroom%2Freleases%2Fwhd%2Fwhd20240104%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epress%20release%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20restaurants%20also%20deducted%20break%20time%20from%20workers'%20schedules%20regardless%20of%20whether%20they%20actually%20took%20a%20break%2C%20deleted%20portions%20of%20their%20shifts%20from%20pay%20records%2C%20and%20didn't%20pay%20staff%20overtime%20where%20necessary.%20This%20led%20to%20violations%20of%20federal%20minimum%20wage%20and%20overtime%20laws%20under%20the%20Fair%20Labor%20Standards%20Act%2C%20the%20DOL%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20restaurants%20were%20operated%20by%20Checkerboard%20Montgomery%20LLC%20and%20Checkerboard%20Montgomery%202%20LLC.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20DOL%20said%20it%20had%20recovered%20%2426%2C927%20in%20back%20wages%20and%20liquidated%20damages%20for%2036%20employees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWilful%20and%20illegal%20actions%20such%20as%20these%20cannot%20be%20ignored%20as%20they%20deprive%20workers%20of%20their%20rights%20and%20make%20it%20more%20difficult%20for%20employers%20who%20follow%20the%20law%20to%20be%20successful%2C%26quot%3B%20Kenneth%20Stripling%2C%20district%20director%20for%20the%20DOL's%20Wage%20and%20Hour%20Division%20in%20Birmingham%2C%20Alabama%2C%20said%20in%20the%20press%20release.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20wasn't%20the%20first%20time%20the%20DOL%20had%20found%20wage%20violations%20at%20the%20franchisees'%20restaurants.%20The%20department%20said%20that%20the%20owners%20of%20the%20franchisees%20owed%20%243%2C636%20in%20civil%20money%20penalties%20for%20the%20%26quot%3Brepeated%20nature%26quot%3B%20of%20the%20violations%2C%20referring%20to%20an%20investigation%20in%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20DOL%20also%20assessed%20Checkerboard%20Montgomery%20LLC%20and%20Checkerboard%20Montgomery%202%20LLC%20%245%2C228%20in%20civil%20money%20penalties%20for%20violating%20child-labor%20laws%20by%20allowing%2015-year-old%20employees%20to%20work%20more%20hours%20than%20permitted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECheckers%20and%20Rally's%20merged%20in%201999%2C%20with%20many%20geographies%20having%20just%20one%20of%20the%20two%20drive-thru%20burger%20chains%20in%20operation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcheckerboardfood.com%2Flocations%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewebsite%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Checkerboard%20Foods%2C%20which%20is%20owned%20by%20the%20same%20people%20as%20Checkerboard%20Montgomery%20LLC%2C%20owns%2010%20Checkers%20and%20Rally's%20restaurants%20in%20Alabama%20and%20Florida.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENeither%20Checkers%20nor%20the%20franchisees%20immediately%20replied%20to%20requests%20for%20comment%20from%20Business%20Insider%2C%20sent%20outside%20regular%20business%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcheckers-restaurants-alabama-montgomery-clocked-staff-out-while-working-dol-2024-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704712833000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F659bd23c6979d7371821288f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcheckers-restaurants-alabama-montgomery-clocked-staff-out-while-working-dol-2024-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20restaurants%20also%20deducted%20break%20time%20f