0to%20make%20the%20drive%20to%20visit%20us%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20so%20isolating.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20now%20have%201%2C500%20fewer%20square%20feet%20of%20living%20space%2C%20one%20fewer%20car%2C%20and%20no%20yard%2C%20but%20they're%20much%20happier.%20They're%20surrounded%20by%20restaurants%2C%20live%20music%2C%20parks%2C%20and%20many%20other%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Floneliness-epidemic-decline-in-third-places-friends-parks-community-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ethird%20places%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20to%20meet%20people%20and%20hang%20out.%20They're%20regulars%20at%20their%20favorite%20neighborhood%20bar%20and%20bodega%2C%20where%2C%20Sutton%20says%2C%20%26quot%3Bwe%20know%20everyone%20by%20name%20and%20vice%20versa.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20couple%20could%20afford%20to%20return%20to%20the%20city%20in%20part%20because%20they're%20DINKS%3A%20double%20income%2C%20no%20kids.%20They%20won't%20need%20the%20extra%20bedrooms%2C%20pricey%20daycares%2C%20or%20outdoor%20space%20that%20would%20crush%20their%20budget.%20Sutton's%20right%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0they%20are%20lucky.%20Many%20millennials%20hoping%20to%20buy%20a%20home%20and%20have%20kids%20are%20being%20priced%20out%20of%20the%20urban%20neighborhoods%20they've%20built%20their%20lives%20in%20and%20that%20were%20reshaped%20to%20fit%20their%20lives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20homebuyers%20who%20decamped%20for%20the%20suburbs%20in%20the%20horrifying%20first%20months%20of%20the%20pandemic%20have%20come%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famericans-regretting-moves-from-city-to-suburbs-housing-crisis-millennials-2023-11%23%3A~%3Atext%3DFor%2520many%2520millennial%2520homebuyers%2520in%2Cassimilate%2520into%2520their%2520new%2520communities.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eregret%20their%20move%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20as%20housing%20costs%20and%20mortgage%20rates%20hit%20record%20highs%2C%20they're%20stuck.%20Those%20who%20stayed%20in%20the%20cities%20are%20fleeing%20in%20droves%2C%20to%20parts%20unknown.%20Millennial%20homebuyers%20aren't%20just%20leaving%20the%20urban%20core%20%E2%80%94%20they're%20moving%20to%20the%20farthest%20reaches%20of%20the%20suburbs.%20The%20housing%20market%20and%20aging%20(the%20oldest%20millennials%20are%20entering%20their%20mid-40s%2C%20SMH)%20are%20turning%20millennials%20into%20the%20thing%20every%20generation%20swears%20they'll%20never%20become%3A%20their%20suburban%20parents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20'youthification'%20of%20cities%20and%20far-flung%20suburbs%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20nearly%20two%20decades%20millennials%20morphed%20dense%2C%20amenity-rich%20urban%20neighborhoods%20across%20America%20into%20exclusive%20playgrounds%20for%20the%20young%20and%20childless.%20Compared%20with%20Gen%20Xers%20and%20baby%20boomers%2C%20a%20much%20larger%20share%20of%20millennials%20moved%20to%20cities%20in%20their%20young%20adulthood%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0and%20stayed%20for%20longer.%20They%20wanted%20craft-cocktail%20bars%20over%20picket%20fences%2C%20walkable%20commutes%20over%20two-car%20garages%2C%20SoulCycle%20over%20swimming%20pools.%20In%20turn%2C%20cities%20were%20yassified%20in%20their%20image.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20%26quot%3Byouthification%26quot%3B%20trend%20has%20accelerated%3A%20Cities%20are%20getting%20younger%2C%20faster%2C%20from%20San%20Francisco%20to%20Boston%2C%20Salt%20Lake%20City%20to%20Seattle%2C%20Austin%20to%20Denver.%20But%20it's%20not%20millennials%20who%20are%20making%20them%20younger%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0it's%20Gen%20Zers.%20(Gen%20Z%2C%20it%20should%20be%20noted%2C%20isn't%20exactly%20thriving%20in%20urban%20real-estate%20markets.%20About%20a%20third%20of%20Gen%20Z%20adults%20are%20thought%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2022%2F07%2F21%2Frealestate%2Fadult-children-living-at-home.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Elive%20with%20their%20parents%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20many%20don't%20think%20they'll%20ever%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2Finteractive%2F2023%2F08%2F10%2Frealestate%2Fgen-z-rent-homeowner.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ebe%20able%20to%20own%20a%20home%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.)%20Millennials%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20are%20aging%20out%20and%20getting%20priced%20out%20into%20suburbia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERecently%2C%20the%20Suburban%20Jungle%20Group%2C%20a%20real-estate%20advisory%20firm%20that%20specializes%20in%20helping%20New%20York%20City%20dwellers%20move%20to%20surrounding%20suburbs%2C%20has%20been%20getting%20a%20lot%20of%20calls%20from%20millennials%20freaking%20out%20as%20their%20lifestyle%20grows%20out%20of%20reach.%20They%20got%20pandemic-era%20deals%20and%20signed%20two-year%20leases%2C%20and%20they're%20seeing%20their%20rent%20skyrocket.%20%26quot%3BClients%20call%20us%20in%20a%20panic%2C%20saying%2C%20'I%20got%20my%20renewal%2C%20I%20have%2030%20or%2060%20days%20to%20let%20them%20know%2C%20and%20my%20rent%20is%20increasing%20up%20to%2030-plus%20percent%2C'%26quot%3B%20said%20Allison%20Levine%2C%20the%20firm's%20director%20of%20communications.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20pandemic%20only%20steepened%20a%20trend%20that's%20been%20ousting%20millennials%20from%20cities%20for%20years%3A%20rising%20housing%20costs%20in%20cities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202017%2C%20Tiffany%20Stuart%2C%20then%2036%2C%20and%20her%20husband%20left%20New%20York%20City%20and%20moved%20to%20New%20Jersey%20when%20they%20realized%20they%20couldn't%20afford%20a%20larger%20apartment%20for%20their%20growing%20family.%20These%20days%2C%20they%20both%20commute%20an%20hour%20each%20way%20%E2%80%94%20Stuart%20by%20train%20and%20her%20husband%20mostly%20by%20car%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0several%20times%20a%20week.%20Beyond%20tolls%2C%20car%20maintenance%2C%20and%20other%20commuting%20expenses%2C%20Stuart%20is%20frustrated%20by%20the%20other%20costs%20of%20owning%20a%20home%2C%20like%20leaky%20roofs%20and%20lawn%20care.%20Though%20she%20appreciates%20the%20greenery%20and%20her%20friendly%20neighbors%2C%20she%20misses%20aspects%20of%20city%20life%2C%20particularly%20all%20the%20West%20Indian%20restaurants%20she%20grew%20up%20around%20in%20Flatbush.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20COVID-19%20shut%20down%20much%20of%20the%20country%2C%20millions%20of%20people%20were%20suddenly%20living%20their%20entire%20lives%20in%20their%20cramped%20apartments%2C%20and%20demand%20for%20larger%20homes%20shot%20up.%20And%20since%20there%20aren't%20enough%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.vox.com%2Fpolicy%2F2023%2F4%2F23%2F23686130%2Fhousing-apartments-family-yimby-nimby-zoning-suburbs%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Efamily-sized%20apartments%20in%20urban%20areas%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20keep%20up%20with%20demand%2C%20in%20part%20because%20studios%20and%20one-bedrooms%20are%20more%20profitable%20for%20developers%20to%20build%2C%20that%20demand%20shot%20up%20in%20the%20suburbs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECensus%20data%20indicates%20that%20in%202022%20adults%20between%2020%20and%2029%20were%20more%20likely%20to%20say%20they%20moved%20for%20housing-related%20reasons%20than%20for%20family-%20or%20employment-related%20reasons.%20Hyojung%20Lee%20and%20his%20colleagues%20at%20Harvard's%20Joint%20Center%20for%20Housing%20Studies%20have%20found%20that%20cities%20with%20the%20most%20expensive%20rents%20and%20the%20smallest%20shares%20of%20apartments%20with%20three%20or%20more%20bedrooms%20lost%20the%20largest%20shares%20of%20their%20millennial%20population%20to%20the%20suburbs%20in%20recent%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20Lee%20and%20his%20colleagues'%20surprise%2C%20millennials%20aren't%20moving%20to%20nearby%20dense%2C%20walkable%20exurbs.%20They're%20getting%20%3Cem%3Eway%20out%3C%2Fem%3E%20to%20peripheral%20suburbs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20turned%20out%20that%20millennials%20are%20moving%20to%20the%20most%20boring%20places%20in%20the%20world%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Lee%2C%20who's%20now%20a%20professor%20at%20Seoul%20National%20University.%20%26quot%3BThey're%20moving%20to%20really%20single-family-dominated%20areas%20with%20very%20few%20urban%20amenities.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJohn%20Natale%2C%20a%20real-estate%20agent%20based%20in%20Wall%20Township%2C%20New%20Jersey%2C%20calls%20this%20phenomenon%20%26quot%3Bdrive%20till%20you%20qualify.%26quot%3B%20He%20says%20it%20used%20to%20be%20that%20he%20could%20find%20his%20clients%20a%20home%20in%20their%20price%20range%20in%20whichever%20county%20they%20wanted%20to%20be%20in.%20Now%2C%20because%20prices%20in%20exurbs%20have%20swelled%20since%202022%2C%20his%20millennial%20clients%20are%20being%20priced%20out%20of%20anything%20within%20striking%20distance%20of%20New%20York.%20%26quot%3BPeople%20are%20adjusting%20one%2C%20two%2C%20maybe%20even%20three%20counties%20over%20just%20to%20be%20able%20to%20afford%20a%20house%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERafay%20Qamar%2C%20a%20real-estate%20agent%20in%20Chicago%2C%20says%20many%20of%20his%20millennial%20clients%20who%20left%20the%20city%20to%20buy%20homes%20in%20the%20suburbs%20in%20recent%20years%20are%20trying%20to%20come%20back.%20%26quot%3BSome%20of%20these%20were%20rash%20decisions%20because%20properties%20were%20moving%20so%20aggressively%2C%20so%20quickly.%20People%20didn't%20really%20have%20a%20chance%20to%20shop%20around%2C%26quot%3B%20Qamar%20said.%20%26quot%3BIn%20about%20a%20year%20or%20so%20they're%20like%2C%20'Listen%2C%20work%20just%20opened%20up%2C%20and%20this%20commute%20is%20terrible.%20We've%20got%20to%20sell%20it%20and%20go%20back%20to%20the%20city.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20in%20this%20housing%20market%2C%20many%20are%20stuck.%20They%20can't%20afford%20to%20sell%20their%20suburban%20homes%2C%20some%20of%20which%20have%20depreciated%20since%20the%20market%20highs%20in%202021%20and%202022%2C%20particularly%20with%20mortgage%20rates%20so%20elevated.%20%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20people%20are%20now%20underwater%2C%26quot%3B%20Qamar%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20urban%20affordability%20crisis%20is%20hitting%20all%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwealthy-millennials-buying-homes-cities-versus-suburbs-exurbs-2021-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ebut%20the%20wealthiest%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20As%20lower-income%20people%20were%20priced%20out%20of%20cities%2C%20the%20rate%20of%20suburban%20poverty%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsuburban-areas-poverty-rising-faster-than-cities-post-pandemic-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Erose%20three%20times%20as%20fast%20as%20the%20rate%20of%20urban%20poverty%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%202019%20to%202022.%20Black%20families%20have%20been%20particularly%20affected.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F01%2F31%2Fnyregion%2Fblack-residents-nyc.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ENew%20York%20City%20lost%20about%209%25%20of%20its%20Black%20residents%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20over%20the%20past%2020%20years%20and%20more%20than%2019%25%20of%20its%20Black%20children%20and%20teens%20from%202010%20to%202020.%20It's%20part%20of%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fnation%2F2022%2F01%2F14%2Fblack-migration-south%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ebroader%20trend%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20dubbed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.brookings.edu%2Farticles%2Fa-new-great-migration-is-bringing-black-americans-back-to-the-south%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ea%20%26quot%3BNew%20Great%20Migration%2C%26quot%3B%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20Black%20families%20leaving%20expensive%20northern%20cities%20for%20the%20suburbs%20and%20for%20the%20South%2C%20where%20the%20cost%20of%20living%20is%20lower.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20roundabout%20way%20to%20more%20walkable%20communities%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20expensive%20to%20live%20in%20the%20places%20millennials%20prefer%3A%20walkable%20communities%20with%20lots%20of%20shops%2C%20restaurants%2C%20and%20public%20space.%20An%20analysis%20published%20last%20year%20found%20that%20homebuyers%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsmartgrowthamerica.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2FFoot-Traffic-Ahead-2023.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ein%20the%2035%20biggest%20American%20metropolitan%20areas%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20paid%2034%25%20more%20to%20live%20in%20walkable%20neighborhoods%2C%20while%20renters%20paid%2041%25%20more.%20Paul%20Stout%2C%20a%20millennial%20landscape-architecture%20student%20with%20a%20popular%20urbanist%20TikTok%20account%20called%20Talking%20Cities%2C%20says%20he%20constantly%20hears%20from%20followers%20who%20wish%20they%20could%20afford%20a%20home%20within%20walking%20distance%20of%20places%20like%20coffee%20shops.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20can't%20emphasize%20enough%20how%20many%20times%20I%20read%20comments%20with%20people%20saying%20that%20they%20wish%20they%20could%20live%20somewhere%20more%20walkable%20but%20they%20just%20simply%20can't%20afford%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Stout%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20while%20millennials%20wallow%20over%20the%20choice%20between%20a%20tiny%20apartment%20in%20a%20dense%20city%20and%20a%20lonely%2C%20sidewalk-less%20subdivision%2C%20urbanists%20insist%20any%20place%20can%20be%20dense%20and%20walkable%20as%20long%20as%20land-use%20laws%20allow%20it%20and%20people%20want%20to%20live%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20lot%20of%20places%20in%20the%20suburbs%20that%20could%20be%20really%20lovely%20to%20live%20if%20you%20could%20only%20put%20a%20grocery%20store%20or%20a%20coffee%20shop%20on%20the%20corner%2C%26quot%3B%20Stout%20says.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20optimistic%20that%20you%20could%20actually%20make%20living%20walkable%20almost%20anywhere%20in%20the%20US%2C%20given%20the%20right%20package%20of%20zoning%20reform.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZoning%20codes%20and%20other%20land-use%20regulations%20are%20controlled%20by%20local%20voters%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0and%2C%20particularly%20in%20suburbia%2C%20they%20tend%20to%20be%20older%20homeowners%20with%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdcist.com%2Fstory%2F22%2F04%2F05%2Fmontgomery-md-housing-affordability-neighborhood-defenders%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Epenchant%20for%20the%20status%20quo%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Tayana%20Panova%2C%20an%20urban%20researcher%20writing%20a%20book%20about%20suburbia's%20effects%20on%20mental%20health%2C%20said%20an%20influx%20of%20younger%20%26quot%3Bcity-craving%26quot%3B%20homeowners%20and%20voters%20could%20change%20that%2C%20but%20only%20if%20they%20engaged%20themselves%20in%20the%20politics%20of%20it%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMillennials%20could%20help%20transform%20suburban%20sprawl%20into%20town-like%20communities%20or%20small%20cities%20with%20more%20third%20places%20and%20a%20stronger%20sense%20of%20community%2C%20Panova%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20some%20places%2C%20it's%20already%20happening.%20%26quot%3BEven%20the%20farthest-flung%20suburbs%20are%20starting%20to%20see%20some%20of%20the%20impacts%20of%20their%20new%20millennial%20residents.%20Many%20that%20gained%20a%20significant%20number%20of%20new%20millennial%20residents%20are%20also%20becoming%20more%20amenity-rich%2C%26quot%3B%20Lee%20said.%20Suburban%20retail%20is%20booming%20%E2%80%94%20half%20of%20Sweetgreen%20salad%20shops%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Farticles%2Fthe-decline-of-the-five-day-commute-is-a-boon-to-suburban-retail-55e4dc89%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eare%20now%20in%20the%20suburbs%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20up%20from%2035%25%20four%20years%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20are%20so%20many%20towns%20that%20in%20the%20last%20five%2C%20six%20years%20I've%20seen%20huge%20revitalizations%2C%20where%20all%20of%20a%20sudden%20restaurants%20and%20exercise%20studios%20and%20trendy%20stores%20start%20to%20pop%20up%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Levine%20of%20Suburban%20Jungle.%20%26quot%3BYou%20can%20move%20to%20the%20suburbs%20and%20not%20feel%20like%20you%20need%20to%20go%20to%20the%20city%20to%20have%20a%20great%20dinner%20or%20to%20see%20a%20show%20or%20live%20music%20or%20the%20arts.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPanova%20says%20this%20could%20be%20%26quot%3Ba%20turning%20point%26quot%3B%20for%20suburban%20communities%20with%20a%20burgeoning%20millennial%20population%20that%20%26quot%3Bmakes%20them%20more%20city-like.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20we%20can%20plant%20those%20kinds%20of%20urban%20seeds%20that%20grow%20into%20little%20communities%2C%20that%20would%20be%20a%20great%20way%20to%20ease%20the%20pressure%20on%20these%20handful%20of%20cities%20that%20are%20getting%20all%20the%20incoming%20traffic%20of%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIndeed%2C%20if%20the%20restaurants%2C%20bars%2C%20and%20cultural%20institutions%20near%20Sutton's%20home%20in%20Nashville%20had%20been%20as%20easily%20accessible%20when%20she%20lived%20in%20the%20suburbs%2C%20she%20said%2C%20she%20might%20never%20have%20felt%20the%20pull%20back%20to%20the%20city.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Feliza-relman%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EEliza%20Reman%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20reports%20on%20housing%2C%20transportation%2C%20and%20cities%20for%20Business%20Insider's%20Economy%20team.%3Cbr%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennials-priced-out-of-cities-into-suburbs-housing-crisis-2024-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704711241000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65985ae76979d7371820eede%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennials-priced-out-of-cities-into-suburbs-housing-crisis-2024-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Goodbye%2C%20SoulCycle%2