0states%20should%20get%20a%20%E2%80%9Cslightly%20larger%20portion%E2%80%9D%20of%20funds%20from%20the%20Union%20government%20through%20a%20%E2%80%9Crecorrection%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%20fiscal%20range%20to%20avoid%20%E2%80%9Cdisaffection%E2%80%9D%20from%20growing%2C%20especially%20if%20the%20political%20representation%20of%20these%20states%20change%20post%20the%20delimitation%20exercise%20in%202026%2C%20former%20Chief%20Economic%20Advisor%20(CEA)%20Arvind%20Subramanian%20said%20on%20Sunday%20(January%207).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDeccan%20Herald%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Findia%2Ftamil-nadu%2Fsouthern-states-should-get-slightly-larger-portion-of-funds-from-centre-arvind-subramanian-2839000%5C%22%3Equoted%20him%20as%20saying%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20wedge%20between%20fiscal%20power%20and%20contribution%20and%20political%20power%20is%20going%20to%20rise.%20However%2C%20he%20expressed%20hope%20that%20the%2016th%20Finance%20Commission%20will%20address%20these%20critical%20issues.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIf%2C%20for%20example%2C%20the%20political%20representation%20is%20changed%2C%20which%20gives%20more%20relative%20power%20to%20the%20Hindi%20Heartland%20relative%20to%20the%20Southern%20states%20that%20have%20slower%20population%20growth%2C%20the%20disaffection%20will%20grow%20because%20the%20Southern%20states%20will%20say%20we%20contribute%20much%20more%20fiscally%20(but)%20we%20are%20losing%20political%20power%2C%E2%80%9D%20Subramanian%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSouthern%20states%2C%20including%20Tamil%20Nadu%2C%20should%20retain%20a%20slightly%20larger%20portion%20of%20resources%20that%20are%20coming%20from%20the%20Centre.%20I%20think%20that%20has%20to%20be%20part%20of%20the%20new%20social%20contract%20going%20forward%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20former%20CEA%20made%20these%20comments%20at%20an%20interactive%20session%2C%20in%20which%20another%20former%20CEA%20and%20former%20Reserve%20Bank%20of%20India%20governor%20Raghuram%20Rajan%20were%20also%20present.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERajan%2C%20who%20is%20also%20advising%20the%20Tamil%20Nadu%20government%20like%20Subramanian%2C%20said%20India%20is%20too%20big%20to%20be%20run%20only%20from%20New%20Delhi.%20He%20called%20for%20more%20finances%20to%20the%20states%20which%20are%20investing%20in%20huge%20infrastructure%20and%20social%20projects.%20He%20said%20that%20the%20issue%20between%20the%20Union%20government%20and%20states%20was%20that%20the%20former%20is%20raising%20a%20lot%20through%20cess%20which%20is%20not%20being%20shared%20with%20the%20latter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThat%20is%20the%20problem.%20I%20think%20the%2014th%20Finance%20commission%20tried%20to%20devolve%20more%20to%20the%20states%2C%20but%20we%20have%20got%20more%20towards%20the%20Centre%20slightly%20in%20the%2015th%20Finance%20commission%E2%80%A6States%20are%20extremely%20important%20and%20we%20need%20to%20devolve%20more%20finances%20to%20the%20states%20and%20(ensure)%20a%20steady%20devolution%20of%20funds%2C%E2%80%9D%20Rajan%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESubramanian%20and%20Rajan%E2%80%99s%20remarks%20come%20amid%20concerns%20among%20southern%20states%20that%20their%20allocation%20from%20the%20Centre%20has%20diminished%20over%20the%20years.%20They%20perceive%20a%20potential%20consequence%20for%20managing%20population%20growth%2C%20expressing%20concerns%20about%20a%20potential%20decrease%20in%20the%20number%20of%20parliamentary%20seats%20following%20the%202026%20delimitation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeparately%2C%20speaking%20on%20the%20China%2B1%20strategy%2C%20Rajan%20said%20that%20India%20was%20attracting%20much%20less%20investments%20than%20it%20was%20thought%20to%20be%20as%20a%20lot%20of%20investments%20are%20going%20to%20countries%20like%20Vietnam%20and%20Mexico%2C%20which%20according%20to%20him%2C%20were%20scoring%20because%20of%20more%20regional%20trade%20agreements.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIndia%2C%20as%20a%20country%2C%20needs%20to%20focus%20more%20on%20this.%20How%20do%20we%20get%20more%20of%20that%20kind%20of%20flow%20which%20would%20mean%20negotiating%20more%20of%20these%20regional%20trade%20agreements%20from%20which%20of%20course%20states%20like%20Tamil%20Nadu%20will%20benefit%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20India%20was%20losing%20out%20despite%20its%20advantages%20like%20huge%20manpower%20and%20domestic%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESubramanian%20and%20Rajan%20further%20said%20that%20the%20state%20government%20should%20pay%20attention%20to%20the%20debt%2C%20especially%20in%20the%20power%20sector%2C%20which%20is%20one-third%20of%20the%20total%20debt%20of%20Tamil%20Nadu.%20They%20also%20lauded%20the%20state%20government%20for%20initiating%20reforms%20in%20several%20sectors%20like%20increasing%20the%20property%20taxes%20and%20indexing%20them%20with%20inflation.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704695444000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F04%2F05161643%2F25864047814_2d77293f02_k.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fsouthern-states-should-retain-slightly-larger-portion-of-funds-from-centre-arvind-subramanian%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20former%20CEA's%20remarks%20come%20amid%20concerns%20among%20southern%20states%20that%20their%20allocation%20from%20the%20Union%20government%20has%20diminished%20over%20the%20years.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A6%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fsouthern-states-should-retain-slightly-larger-portion-of-funds-from-centre-arvind-subramanian%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22No%20adverse%20findings%20in%20Boeing%20737%20Max%20planes%2C%20says%20Akasa%20post-inspection%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704695075000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2022-10%2F15%2Ffull%2F1665827637-6325.jpg%22%2