quentially%20law%20has%20been%20invented%20in%20place%20of%20constitutionalism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20are%20told%20that%20there%20is%20an%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22internal%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheleaflet.in%2Fhindu-dharma-has-taken-over-constitutional-values-says-indira-jaising-at-the-sixth-neelabh-mishra-lecture%2F%5C%22%3Eintrinsic%20dharma%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20people%20of%20India%20which%20is%20ancient%20and%20predates%20the%20Constitution.%20Once%20a%20norm%20above%20the%20Constitution%20is%20created%2C%20it%20is%20easy%20to%20see%20why%20there%20is%20no%20need%20to%20amend%20the%20Constitution.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDelhi%20University%20professor%20Apoorvanand%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fchandrachud-orator-courtroom-judgments-babri-ayodhya%5C%22%3Ealso%20opined%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20how%20CJI%20Chandrachud%20appears%20to%20be%20moving%20away%20from%20his%20job%20of%20dispensing%20justice%2C%20and%20instead%20focusing%20on%20the%20speeches%20he%20makes%20and%20messages%20he%20spreads%20outside%20of%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704692274000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F08110652%2FGDI_UsnWYAA-QMc.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fcji-invokes-dhwaja-on-temples-to-serve-as-inspiration-for-courts-draws-attention%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22PM%20Narendra%20Modi%20shared%20Chief%20Justice%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%E2%80%99s%20speech%20as%20an%20example%20of%20understanding%20Rajkot%20%E2%80%9Cvery%20well!%E2%80%9D%20Public%20intellectuals%20have%20raised%20serious%20questions%20over%20the%20implications%20of%20such%20statements.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A9%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fcji-invokes-dhwaja-on-temples-to-serve-as-inspiration-for-courts-draws-attention%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22SC%20Quashes%20Gujarat%20Govt's%20Release%20of%20Bilkis%20Bano%20Convicts%2C%20Orders%20Their%20Return%20to%20Prison%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F08102157%2FUntitled-design-1.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20said%20that%20the%20Gujarat%20government%20does%20not%20have%20the%20power%20to%20grant%20premature%20release%20of%2011%20convicts%20who%20had%20been%20sentenced%20to%20life%20for%20gang-raping%20a%20pregnant%20Bilkis%20Bano%2C%20members%20of%20her%20family%2C%20and%20also%20mass%20murdering%20at%20least%2014%20of%20them%20in%20the%202002%20Gujarat%20riots.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20has%20asked%20the%20convicts%20to%20surrender%20back%20to%20prison%20within%20two%20weeks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Gujarat%20government%20%E2%80%93%20under%20the%20same%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20which%20was%20in%20power%20during%20the%20riots%20%E2%80%93%20had%20announced%20the%20decision%20to%20grant%20the%2011%20men%20premature%20release%20on%20August%2015%2C%20Independence%20Day%2C%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20division%20bench%20of%20Justices%20B.V.%20Nagarathna%20and%20Ujjal%20Bhuyan%20said%20that%20the%20state%20of%20Gujarat%20%E2%80%9Cacted%20in%20complicity%20with%20the%20convicts%E2%80%9D%20and%20noted%20that%20%E2%80%9Cit%20was%20this%20very%20apprehension%20which%20led%20this%20Court%20to%20transfer%20the%20trial%20out%20of%20the%20State%E2%80%9D%20to%20Maharashtra.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20scathing%20judgment%2C%20the%20court%20also%20noted%20that%20if%20the%20convicts%20can%20%E2%80%9Ccircumvent%20the%20consequences%20of%20their%20conviction%2C%20peace%20and%20tranquillity%20in%20the%20society%20will%20be%20reduced%20to%20a%20chimaera.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98Nullity%20in%20law%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20apex%20court%20has%20now%20held%20that%20the%20judgment%20of%20May%2013%2C%202022%2C%20by%20a%20bench%20of%20Justices%20Ajay%20Rastogi%20and%20Vikram%20Nath%2C%20which%20directed%20the%20Gujarat%20government%20to%20consider%20remission%2C%20%E2%80%9Ca%20nullity%E2%80%9D%20as%20it%20was%20obtained%20by%20%E2%80%9Cplaying%20fraud%20on%20the%20Court%E2%80%9D%20and%20by%20suppressing%20material%20facts.%20%E2%80%9CAll%20proceedings%20taken%20in%20furtherance%20of%20the%20judgment%20are%20also%20vitiated%20and%20a%20nullity%20in%20law%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20court%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20also%20said%20today%20that%20the%20government%20of%20the%20state%20where%20the%20offender%20is%20sentenced%20is%20the%20appropriate%20government%20to%20grant%20remission%2C%20not%20the%20government%20of%20the%20state%20where%20the%20offence%20took%20place%2C%20%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20tweeted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBilkis%20Bano%20is%20one%20of%20the%20several%20petitioners%20who%20challenged%20the%20Gujarat%20government%E2%80%99s%20remission%20of%20the%20convicts%E2%80%99%20sentences.%20The%20court%20held%20today%20that%20since%20Bano%E2%80%99s%20plea%20was%20held%20maintainable%2C%20there%20was%20no%20need%20to%20answer%20whether%20the%20other%20public%20interest%20litigations%20were%20maintainable%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20judgment%20was%20authored%20by%20Justice%20Nagarathna%2C%20who%20while%20reading%20her%20judgment%20on%20January%208%2C%20noted%20that%20the%20four%20points%20which%20arise%20out%20of%20the%20case%20are%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E1.%20Whether%20the%20petition%20filed%20by%20victim%20under%20Article%2032%20are%20maintainable%2C%3Cbr%3E%5Cn2.%20Whether%20the%20public%20interest%20litigations%20assailing%20the%20remission%20order%20maintainable%2C%3Cbr%3E%5Cn3.%20Whether%20the%20Gujarat%20government%20was%20competent%20to%20pass%20the%20remission%20orders%2C%20and%3Cbr%3E%5Cn4.%20Whether%20the%20remission%20orders%20are%20in%20accordance%20with%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98Usurpation%20of%20power%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Nagarathna%20said%2C%20on%20the%20ground%20that%20the%20Gujarat%20government%20lacked%20competence%20alone%2C%20the%20writ%20petitions%20were%20liable%20to%20be%20allowed%20and%20the%20%E2%80%9Corders%20are%20liable%20to%20be%20declared%20as%20nullity.%E2%80%9D%20But%2C%20she%20said%2C%20the%20matter%20does%20not%20end%20there%20as%20reliance%20was%20placed%20on%20an%20earlier%20judgment%20which%20directed%20the%20Gujarat%20government%20to%20consider%20the%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20earlier%20judgement%20%E2%80%9Cis%20contrary%20to%20the%20Constitution%20Bench%20judgment%20in%20the%20%3Cem%3ESriharan%3C%2Fem%3E%20case%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20Supreme%20court%20said%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2FLiveLawIndia%2Fstatus%2F1744231671480660161%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Justice%20Nagarathna%20further%20said%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9Cpower%20to%20grant%20remission%20is%20ultimately%20an%20exercise%20of%20discretion%20by%20the%20authority.%20The%20test%20is%20whether%20the%20authority%20was%20acting%20within%20the%20scope%20of%20powers%20and%20whether%20it%20was%20exercised%20in%20accordance%20with%20law.%20There%20is%20arbitrariness%20if%20there%20is%20non-consideration%20of%20relevant%20factors%2C%20non-application%20of%20mind%2C%20acting%20on%20dictation%2C%20or%20any%20usurpation%20of%20power.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20data-testid%3D%5C%22cellInnerDiv%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Carticle%20data-testid%3D%5C%22tweet%5C%22%20tabindex%3D%5C%220%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%20data-testid%3D%5C%22tweetText%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EUsurpation%20of%20power%20arises%20when%20power%20vested%20in%20one%20authority%20is%20exercised%20by%20another%2C%20the%20judge%20said.%20%E2%80%9CApplying%20the%20principle%20in%20this%20case%2C%20having%20regard%20to%20our%20answer%20of%20%E2%80%9Cappropriate%20power%E2%80%9D%2C%20Gujarat%20government%20exercising%20the%20power%20was%20an%20instance%20of%20usurpation%20of%20power.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%20data-testid%3D%5C%22tweetText%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20noted%20that%20the%20Gujarat%20government%20usurped%20the%20powers%20of%20the%20Maharashtra%20government%2C%20acting%20in%20furtherance%20of%20the%20judgment%20dated%20May%2013%2C%202022.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20was%20the%20State%20of%20Maharashtra%20which%20was%20the%20appropriate%20government%20to%20consider%20the%20remission%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Farticle%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20had%20concluded%20hearings%20in%20the%20case%20on%20October%2012.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGranting%20remission%2C%20the%20Gujarat%20government%20had%20said%20that%20this%20decision%20had%20been%20arrived%20at%20by%20a%20panel%20it%20had%20set%20up%2C%20comprising%20officials%20and%20%E2%80%98social%20workers%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%93%20all%20of%20whom%20were%20BJP%20members%20or%20were%20connected%20with%20it.%20At%20that%20time%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hindustantimes.com%2Findia-news%2Fbilkis-case-convicts-threatened-witnesses-in-past-show-records-101660935225918.html%5C%22%3Eseveral%20of%20the%20accused%20had%20threatened%20witnesses%20while%20on%20temporary%20parole%3C%2Fa%3E.%20One%20panel%20member%2C%20a%20BJP%20MLA%2C%20had%20said%20that%20the%20convicts%20deserved%20to%20be%20released%20because%20they%20were%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fbilkis-rapists-are-brahmins-have-good-values-says-bjp-mla-who-sat-on-panel-that-freed-convicts%5C%22%3EBrahmins%20with%20good%C2%A0%3Cem%3Esanskaars%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E